The [+ ddp_name +] has been one of our closest allies through the course of the Republic.

@ir_strong
on-arrival: ir_relation += 8*(1 - dissent)

Manuel Azaña, the leader of Izquierda Republicana, has been a strong advocate for democratic reform. He represents the progressive middle class and intellectuals of the Republic.

@radical_loss
on-arrival: radical_relation += 5*(1 - dissent)

With the decline of Izquierda Republicana's influence, the Radical Party tries to position itself as a centrist force. The republican parties are electorally in flux, so perhaps our efforts are best spent elsewhere.

However, given the influence of the Radical Party among the other centrist parties [? if president == "Alcalá-Zamora": and with President Alcalá-Zamora ?], it can still be helpful to influence them.

@radical_moribund
on-arrival: radical_relation += 5*(1 - dissent)

The liberal republican parties (both the [+ ddp_name +] and Radical) are electorally weakened, so perhaps our efforts are best spent elsewhere.

However, given their influence among the other centrist parties[? if president == "Alcalá-Zamora": and with President Alcalá-Zamora ?], it can still be helpful to influence them.

@psoe_alone

Whether it is because we *cannot* or *will not*, we do not make ties with other parties at this moment.

